<br>
Dont spread false information. There is a difference between damage you can sustain indefinately (i.e. 100% UPTIME) and damage you cannot sustain indefinately (i.e. 99% UPTIME OR LESS). Just because youre in a group with only 40% uptime, which allows you to have a very high nuking dps in that particular group, doesnt mean thats what your real sustained nuking dps is.<br>
<br>
NO, you cannot sustain that nuking dps you mention indefinately unless you are very uber. Do not say you can, because it all comes down to a simple mathmatical formula:<br>
<br>
Damage per mana * mana regen per second = <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>max sustained dps</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END-->. Keep in mind this is not your true sustained dps, as you will need to spend mana on things other than direct damage. Thiis just your absolute max sustained damage in a theoretically perfect environment. Right click nukes may raise your sustained nuking dps a bit (only on horseback though as  indoors medding and straight nuking is better use of time resources).<br>
<br>
Personally, using fot, i usually deal damage at a rate of roughly 5.2-5.3 damage per second. This will be different for you depending on what nukes, focus items, spec, and aa you have. <br>
<br>
Self buffed, standing, (22 mana/tic) my true sustained nuking dps is only as high as 19 <br>
With rods and horse med (53 mana/tic) it is as high as 45.<br>
With c5 and sp (78 mana/tic) it is as high as 67.<br>
With constant bard song (99 mana/tic) it is as high as 85.<br>
<br>
If you have store pet and pet canni this will also result in increased mana regen which leads to increased dps, however im not really sure by how much. Anyway my point is your true sustained nuking dps isnt going to be anywhere near what you say, unless you are very uber and have a pet enchanter, beastlord, and bard with you at all times :P. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=noonievioletskies>NoonieVioletskies</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Sage</span><br>  Posts: 1480<br> <font color=#333333>(12/17/02 6:19:33 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm32.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=418.topic&index=27>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_exclamation_mark.gif" align=absmiddle>  ..</span><hr size=1> <!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>Those arguments are made from low end, and a lot are not even level 65. The more knowledgable rogues are the ones to read. Remember, these guys are the same ones saying charm is PERFECTLY BALANCED while saying mage pets are not. Take their words with a grain of salt, a very small grain<br>
