<br>
1) Rogues benefit from item haste and song haste, and numerous buffs that would normally not be cast on pet (atk buffs, hp buffs, etc). A rogue with ranger atk buffs and bard haste/atk songs and a good haste item will more than double his DPS.<br>
<br>
2) Although mages can DS, it doesn't stack with druid DS, it's less effective when mob is slowed, and it takes up a buff slot and mana. So it is situational, and not free. All rogue damage is melee, so it's free and stacks with everything.<br>
<br>
3) Spell damage is situational too. You must have the mana, the mob can full/partial resist, you must not aggro, etc. Chain nuking for full dmg with no aggro and nonstop pulls is not very realistic.<br>
<br>
4) Pet effectiveness is situational. Enrage, pathing, mez breaking, and general stupidness of pets affect class balance.<br>
<br>
Put a healer, tank, rogue, mage, bard and ranger in the group or something comparable. Fully buff. Now lets compare a mob with reasonable resists, who enrages. And pull nonstop like a normal xp group. NOW compare situational DPS between rogue and mage over time. This includes the time it takes for mage to med, summon, heal and buff his pet.<br>
<br>
You will see that the balance changes for different group configurations. Add a bard or ranger, rogue DPS skyrockets. Add druid, mage effectiveness lowers (because his DS is mostly replaceable). Add a slower, mage DPS lowers from the DS. Add manamaker, mage potential DPS increases. Add a tank, rogue DPS increases (more backstabs). etc. <br>
<br>
Now play with mobs. Add fire resistant and/or magic resistant mobs. Slow down or speed up pulls. Add mob that enrages (mage backs pet off while rogue backstabs it). etc.<br>
<br>
All you've proved is that DPS is situational and in some cases rogues do more, in others mages do more. And that only talks about DPS, a single factor in balance (sneak/hide, cr, defense, pick lock, etc). Big deal. <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table> </td></tr></table> <table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top">  Page <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm32.showMessageRange?topicID=418.topic&start=1&stop=20>1</a> <b>2</b>  </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm32.showPrevMessage?topicID=418.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm32.showNextMessage?topicID=418.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br><a self href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm32.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=418.topic&index=39><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/softsky/addReply.gif border=0 alt="Add Reply"></a> </td></tr></table><br><table width=95% border=0><td valign="top"><a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm32.threadControl?topicID=418.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/softsky/unread.gif border=0 alt="Topic Control Image"> Topic Commands</a><br> <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm32.subscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=418.topic>Subscribe</a> Click to receive email notification of replies<br>  <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm32.unsubscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=418.topic>Unsubscribe</a> Click to stop receiving email notification of replies<br> </td><td align="right" valign="top"></td></tr><tr align="right"><td colspan=2><form action=http://pub102.ezboard.com/BBSForum.jumpShowForum method=post><table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="1"><tr><td><b>jump to:</b><select name=forumName><option value="themagicianstowerannouncements">Administration<option value="themagicianstowergeneral">General<option value="themagicians